The African Union (AU) has urged Kenya and Somalia to exercise restraint and instead engage in dialogue over the border tension. “I’m following the tensions on the Kenya-Somalia border with concern, and urge the two neighbours to exercise restraint and engage in dialogue in conformity with the #IGAD-led process,” said Moussa Faki Mahamat, the Chairperson of the AU Commission. “Peace on the Kenya-Somalia border is vital to regional stability.” More follows…